      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2-criteria-001",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump — the same device class and geometry as the COU device — under operating conditions spanning the declared envelope (2.0–6.0 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM). Coverage is sparse at mid-range rotational speeds (2000 and 3000 RPM), as explicitly documented in the operating envelope coverage gap statement. Monotonicity analysis and sensitivity studies bound the interpolation uncertainty at these unvalidated speeds. The coverage gap limits confidence to Level 2 rather than Level 3; however, Level 2 is sufficient for MRL 2. This honest accounting of sparse coverage is consistent with the bounded-applicability declaration."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
