      "rationale": "Comprehensive model input uncertainty analysis is not required at MRL 2. Key input uncertainties (inlet flow rate ±5%, fluid viscosity ±3%) are propagated via Monte Carlo in the validation uncertainty quantification, establishing a total uncertainty band of ±8.4% (k=2). This partial propagation is adequate for MRL 2. Geometric tolerances (±0.05 mm) were assessed via sensitivity study and found to contribute < 1.5% to hemolysis prediction uncertainty within the declared applicability constraint. Scoped out per MRL 2 assessment plan."
