    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the CFD hemolysis prediction model (COU1, MRL 2) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels (achievedLevel >= requiredLevel in all cases); (2) 6 factors are appropriately scoped out with documented rationale consistent with MRL 2 requirements; (3) The ContextOfUse explicitly declares a bounded operating envelope (flow rate 2.0–6.0 L/min, speed 1500–3500 RPM, hematocrit 40±5%, temperature 36–38°C) with concrete numerical bounds, and an applicability constraint limiting use to Newtonian blood-analogue fluids within the Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation validity regime; (4) Validation activities span the declared envelope with honest documentation of sparse coverage at mid-range rotational speeds (2000, 3000 RPM); the coverage gap is bounded by monotonicity analysis and sensitivity studies, and is reflected in the achieved Level 2 (rather than Level 3) for validation relevance — adequate for MRL 2; (5) All validation results have comparedAgainst, prov:wasGeneratedBy, and hasUncertaintyQuantification links; (6) Discretization error is well-controlled (GCI 2.7%, asymptotic convergence) and code verification confirms 2nd-order accuracy; (7) CFD predictions are conservatively biased (over-predict hemolysis by 4–13%), ensuring the RHI < 1.0 acceptance criterion is not falsely satisfied; (8) The provenance chain is complete from raw experimental data through simulation activities to validation results and this decision record. The model is fit for its declared purpose within the bounded operating envelope. Extrapolation beyond the declared bounds is explicitly prohibited.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
